Name: Bi-2201
Sentence: (2) The changing volume fractions and morphologies of phases in the melt do not just simply manifest themselves by changing the volume fraction of the Bi-2212 grains formed and the residual AEC and CF in the fully reacted conductors, but also by changing the internal structure of Bi-2212 grain colonies and grain boundaries. 521 conductors have a higher population of Bi-2201 intergrowths whereas 524 conductors are nearly free of them.
Moreover, the J c of Bi-2212 round wires at 4.2 K seems to not be sensitive to their T c , and rather increases with decreasing T c from 92 K to 82 K with increasing oxygen doping .
